  "events": {
    "202507": "Pre-event baseline. Erika Kirk appears in public coverage only as Charlie Kirk's wife, with no independent storyline. GDELT records zero mainstream articles mentioning her by name; social mentions are background noise tied to incidental TPUSA event posts.",
    "202508": "Still pre-event. Charlie Kirk's summer TPUSA tour generates minor coverage but Erika remains incidental. GDELT again records zero mainstream articles; the small composite score comes from a minor topic-overlap mismatch in negligible-volume coverage.",
    "202509": "Charlie Kirk is assassinated September 10 at Utah Valley University. Erika delivers her first public remarks two days later, the TPUSA board names her CEO, and at the funeral she publicly forgives the accused killer. Both channels are saturated with the same set of topics, which is why divergence stays moderate despite the largest volume spike of the year.",
    "202510": "Trump posthumously awards Charlie the Presidential Medal of Freedom in a Rose Garden ceremony on October 14 — mainstream's headline event. Social cycles through fact-checked rumors instead: a false 'Air Force 2' claim and a fabricated $400M Soros lawsuit. The topic agenda starts to fork.",
    "202511": "Erika gives her first TV interview to Jesse Watters on Fox News (November 5) and receives the inaugural Charlie Kirk Legacy Award. Mainstream covers the interview, awards, and TPUSA's courtroom-cameras fight. Social latches onto a 'never dated' moment with circulating receipts and clipped reaction shots.",
    "202512": "TPUSA AmericaFest draws 30,000 attendees, majority women. Charlie's posthumous book launches and Erika endorses JD Vance for 2028. Social is dominated by escalating Candace Owens tensions, the first pregnancy rumors, and early Vance-affair speculation.",
    "202601": "Mainstream covers the Make Heaven Crowded Tour and TPUSA's state expansions. Social is wholly consumed by debunked pregnancy rumors (originating from a satirical 'Hoops Crave' account), an AI-deepfake clip of Erika 'dancing' at Rolling Loud Orlando, and remarriage speculation. Topic overlap drops to zero — the channels have no shared agenda this month.",
    "202602": "Erika fights to keep cameras in the assassin's trial and partners with Montana's governor on TPUSA expansion. Social fixates on a wedding photo being moved off Charlie's office shelf, her absent wedding ring in recent footage, and the first hour-long episode of Candace Owens' 'Bride of Charlie' series. The HF model picks up the biggest sentiment delta of the year (+0.27).",
    "202603": "Trump appoints Erika to the U.S. Air Force Academy Board of Visitors; she's named to TIME100 Next; Hillsdale College announces her as commencement speaker. Druski's 'Conservative Women' parody about her hits 80M+ views on X. Volume asymmetry maxes out at 106× the September baseline — but mainstream tabloids covered the parody too, so topic overlap and sentiment delta were both moderate. Just below the HIGH threshold.",
    "202604": "The White House Correspondents' Dinner is cut short by gunfire on April 25; Erika leaves in tears. She announces a step-back and cancels Make Heaven Crowded Tour appearances. Both channels cover the same dramatic event, which partially re-aligns the agenda and pulls topic overlap back up to 0.30.",
    "202605": "Erika cancels a TPUSA event at the University of Georgia citing 'very serious threats'; the Secret Service subsequently says no credible threats were identified. Mainstream and social diverge on whether the threats narrative is credible. GDELT tone reaches its most negative reading of the entire series (−2.87 raw)."
  },
